s://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>For decades, he criticized the industry’s lax attitudes toward computer security and individual digital privacy. He also developed solutions.</description><dc:creator>John Markoff</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 21:27:18 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Peter G Neumann</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">DARPA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SRI International</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Obituary</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/17/multimedia/00neumann-kjbp/00neumann-kjbp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jim Wilson/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Peter G. Neumann in 2012. At his death, he was still working full time on advanced computer security design being adopted by companies like Google and Microsoft. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Bipartisan Bill Would Impose New Annual Fee on Electric Vehicles</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/19/business/energy-environment/electrc-vehicles-annual-fee-congress.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/19/business/energy-environment/electrc-vehicles-annual-fee-congress.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/19/business/energy-environment/electrc-vehicles-annual-fee-congress.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A House transportation bill introduced this week would require owners of electric cars to pay $130 to cover the cost of road repairs.</description><dc:creator>Jack Ewing</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 09:02:37 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric Cars and Hybrids</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Oil and Gasoline</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Roads and Traffic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Gas Tax</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">House Committee on Transportation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Albert Gore III</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Rick Larsen</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sam Graves</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Legislation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federal Aid</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US and Israeli Attack on Iran</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federalism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tax</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Transportation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Highway Trust Fund</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">House of Representatives</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Congress</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/19/multimedia/19biz-ev-fees-jvbc/19biz-ev-fees-jvbc-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Maddie McGarvey for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Congress is considering imposing a new annual fee on electric vehicles to help pay for road repairs.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>After Elon Musk’s Court Loss Comes the Long Hot A.I. Summer</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/elon-musk-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/elon-musk-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/technology/elon-musk-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Even as protests increase, the collapse of Mr. Musk’s suit against OpenAI and Sam Altman will speed up the artificial intelligence juggernaut.</description><dc:creator>David Streitfeld and Natallie Rocha</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 21:53:29 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Judiciary</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Decisions and Verdicts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Companies</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sam Altman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Oakland CA</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/18/multimedia/00biz-musk-altman-ai-hlkm/00biz-musk-altman-ai-hlkm-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jason Henry for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Elon Musk on Monday lost his lawsuit accusing OpenAI and its chief executive, Sam Altman, of breaching the company’s founding contract.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>